10 county or city, as applicable, to require the nonprofit organization to establish a
11 program to waive the adoption fee of certain pets adopted by a person who is a
12 veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder.
13 Sections 1 and 2 require that these programs: (1) waive the adoption fee for not
14 more than one eligible pet from the animal shelter for a period of 6 months for each
15 veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder who adopts a pet; (2) require
16 such a veteran, law enforcement officer or first responder to provide a valid form of
17 identification; (3) require the animal shelter to report to the governing body of the
18 county or city, as applicable, certain information concerning the program; and (4)
19 require the animal shelter to maintain records of each adoption made under the
20 program. On or before October 1 of each year, the governing body of the county or
21 city is required to submit a report to the Department of Veterans Services
22 containing certain information concerning the program. Section 4 of this bill
23 requires the governing body of the county or incorporated city to submit the first
24 report required by section 1 or 2, as applicable, on or before October 1, 2026.
25 Section 3 of this bill requires the Department to submit a report to the
26 Legislature on or before December 31 of each even-numbered year that compiles
27 the information from the reports the Department received pursuant to sections 1
28 and 2.
