1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. If a county owns and operates an animal shelter, the board
4 of county commissioners shall establish a program to waive the
5 adoption fee of a pet that is 6 months or older, has been at the
6 animal shelter for at least 7 consecutive days and is adopted from
7 the animal shelter by a person who is a veteran, law enforcement
8 officer or first responder.
9 2. If a county does not own and operate an animal shelter,
10 the board of county commissioners shall require, as a condition of
11 any appropriation or contract or other legal agreement with a
12 nonprofit organization that operates an animal shelter in the
13 county, that the animal shelter operated by the nonprofit
14 organization establish a program to waive the adoption fee of a pet
15 at the animal shelter that is 6 months or older, has been at the
16 animal shelter for at least 7 consecutive days and is adopted from
17 the animal shelter by a person who is a veteran, law enforcement
18 officer or first responder.
19 3. A program established pursuant to subsection 1 or 2 must:
20 (a) Waive the adoption fee for not more than one pet that
21 meets the requirements of subsection 1 or 2, as applicable, for a
